time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution first sorts the passengers' arrival times. Then, it iterates over the passengers and for each passenger, it finds the next available bus. If the passenger can get on the bus, it returns the departure time minus one. If the passenger cannot get on the bus, it returns the minimum of the departure time minus one and the arrival time. The solution has a high efficiency due to the sorting of the passengers' arrival times, which reduces the time complexity to O(n log n).

